      "date": "2017-10-19 20:52:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIf for some reason you need to rebase this could you add lockahead_test to .gitignore. Also with new gcc version I see the following build issues:\n\ngcc -DHAVE_CONFIG_H -I. -I../..   -include /usr/src/lustre-2.10.54/undef.h -include /usr/src/lustre-2.10.54/config.h -I/usr/src/lustre-2.10.54/libcfs/include -I/usr/src/lustre-2.10.54/lnet/include -I/usr/src/lustre-2.10.54/lnet/include/uapi -I/usr/src/lustre-2.10.54/lustre/include -I/usr/src/lustre-2.10.54/lustre/include/uapi  -fPIC -D_GNU_SOURCE -D_LARGEFILE64_SOURCE=1 -D_FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64 -DLUSTRE_UTILS=1 -g -O2 -Wall -Werror -c -o lfs.o lfs.c\nlfs.c:5197:26: error: ‘lockahead_results’ defined but not used [-Werror=unused-const-variable=]\n static const char *const lockahead_results[] = {\n                          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\ncc1: all warnings being treated as errors\nMakefile:1265: recipe for target 'lfs.o' failed",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
